<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14088">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Electronics.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13163">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Describe the safety precautions you must exercise when using, building,
      altering, or repairing electronic devices. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/aaE0ePh7zSo" target="_blank"
        >Computer Safety Procedures (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13142">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13142 mb-requirement-id-13143">
        (a) Draw a simple schematic diagram. It must show resistors, capacitors,
        and transistors or integrated circuits. Use the correct symbols. Label
        all parts.<br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9cps7Q_IrX0" target="_blank"
          >Schematics (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_HZ-EQ8Hc8E" target="_blank"
          >How to Read a Schematic (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13142 mb-requirement-id-13144">
        (b) Tell the purpose of each part. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/N8_1wb0r0DQ" target="_blank"
          >Electronic Components Guide (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.tiktok.com/@jyhhsuelectronics/video/7457467056598977838"
          target="_blank"
          >10 Common Electronic Components (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13145">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13145 mb-requirement-id-13146">
        (a) Show the right way to solder and desolder. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-qk-ulz05J8" target="_blank"
          >Using Solder | Soldering Basics | Soldering for Beginners (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bG7yW9FigJA" target="_blank"
          >How to Desolder (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13145 mb-requirement-id-13147">
        (b) Show how to avoid heat damage to electronic components. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/fYk07LcnkPA" target="_blank"
          >Applying Heat to your Parts (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13145 mb-requirement-id-13148">
        (c) Tell about the function of a printed circuit board. Tell what
        precautions should be observed when soldering printed circuit boards.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/BJ3N8gURA1c?si=5Oew7Ys1qIhVBUlP"
          target="_blank"
          >What Are Printed Circuit Boards (PCBs)? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13149">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13149 mb-requirement-id-13150">
        (a) Discuss each of the following with your counselor:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13150 mb-requirement-id-13151">
        (1) How to use electronics for a control purpose. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/oxNmKS6etGM" target="_blank"
          >Inputs, Outputs and Controllers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13150 mb-requirement-id-13152">
        (2) Explain the basic principles of digital logic. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/INEtYZqtjTo" target="_blank"
          >Understanding Logic Gates (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13150 mb-requirement-id-13153">
        (3) How to use electronics for three different analog applications.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13149 mb-requirement-id-13158">
        (b) Show how to change three decimal numbers into binary numbers and
        three binary numbers into decimal numbers. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/a2FpnU9Mm3E" target="_blank"
          >How to Convert Binary to Decimal (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/OYP0pa50a0Q" target="_blank"
          >Convert Decimal to Binary (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13149 mb-requirement-id-13154">
        (c) Choose ONE of the following THREE projects. For your project, find
        or create a schematic diagram. To the best of your ability, explain to
        your counselor how the circuit you built operates. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MxRGXIe1qPo" target="_blank"
          >How to Read an Electronic Schematic (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13154 mb-requirement-id-13155">
        (1) A control device
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13154 mb-requirement-id-13156">
        (2) A digital circuit
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13154 mb-requirement-id-13157">
        (3) An analog circuit
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13159">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13159 mb-requirement-id-13160">
        (a) Show how to solve a simple problem involving current, voltage, and
        resistance using Ohm's law. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KMaQYdTJul0" target="_blank"
          >Ohm's Law Formula (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/uZ-m91IEkjQ" target="_blank"
          >What is OHM'S Law? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13159 mb-requirement-id-13161">
        (b) Tell about the need for and the use of test equipment in
        electronics. Name three types of test equipment. Tell how they operate.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZuFlJ1IZyPs" target="_blank"
          >Circuits &amp; Electronics - Electronics Lab Introduction (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13159 mb-requirement-id-13162">
        (c) Demonstrate to your counselor how to read the colored bands of a
        resistor to determine its resistance value. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GLD7AgAYqwA" target="_blank"
          >How to Read a Resistor (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13159 mb-requirement-id-13165">
        (d) Explain the differences between Through Hole and Surface Mount
        assembly technologies and give three advantages of each. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RW9NO6H62oY" target="_blank"
          >Through Hole vs Surface Mount Method? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13164">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Identify three career opportunities that would use skills and knowledge in
      electronics. Pick one and research the training, education, certification
      requirements, experience, and expenses associated with entering the field.
      Research the prospects for employment, starting salary, advancement
      opportunities and career goals associated with this career. Discuss what
      you learned with your counselor and whether you might be interested in
      this career. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/paEw8Y8WlNA" target="_blank"
        >Careers in Electronics Engineering (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
